review_blob: Nice sturdy head, with lacing.  Deep golden cooper hue, subtle alchol up front breaking to a yeasty middle ending with linger snap.
Definately taste the banana and citrus.  This is a great wheat beer.  Kudos to the Pony Express folks for using homegrown wheat that their farmers/owners grow.
Three or four of these and you have a buzz and a headache.  Not a fan of the Dry expereince.
Not so great.  The Matt Brewing Co makes excellent beer. This throw back to pre prohibition days is not an example of their talent.
The price should give you an idea on the taste.  You pay more for deposit than for the beer.
This beer is named after a river (Genesee) that runs through Rochester NY.  What do you think it taste like?
This is a good change up from the Genny Red Eyes, but still, if youre not eating a plate of suicide wings you may have to actually taste the beer.
The pride of western new york.  Go Bills.  Go Sabres.  Go to Canada and buys some better beer.
Miller is buying all of the top notch brews. If you pay more than $5 for a suitcase of Hamms you were robbed.
Boy oh boy Dad sure drinks some nasty beer.  I think with the mail in rebate they must have paid him to drink it.

Make sure you get a fresh batch.  This is a small brewer that takes pride in their work.  Unfortunately, some store owners in the Copaco Farms Shopping center choose not to rotate the stock.  This is a very good beer when its fresh.
beer_name: Olde Burnside St. Andrews Summer Ale

review_blob: This only comes in growlers and there are no complaints. Quite tasty.  Its all about flavor.  They apparently use high quality water as the base.
I enjoyed this beer on draft when I was in Gardiner MT. Im not usually a Pale Ale drinker but I always enjoy the local beers when I can.  This was quite tasty.
This was a bit heavy on the nut meg/cinamon aroma. I think Jim may have poured some egg nog in the batch.
Yuck, Yuck, Yuck- 1 800 222 1222 Mr Yuk.  Drink some mable syrup, prune juice and rubbing alcohol and you have a taste of this creation. The bottle was sorta cool.  Not worth the money.
Great anytime beer.  I not my first choice in the Sam Adams stable but a throughbred none the less.
This is the prize of the sampler.  Nutmeg, cinamon, fig aroma. It took a few sampler packs before I truly sought this out.
This one is Great in the sampler and its been even better on draft. Im a Sam Adams fan.

This is a great light beer.  I typically only drink light beer when my wife goes shopping.  I would say Amstel light is better since it does not taste as watered down.  I rated this compared to full bodied beers.
I am enjoying this beer right now.  It has  lingering chemical taste that breaks into a walnut muffin pleasantness
I really enjoyed this beer when I went to Yellowstone.  A word of caution- elevation does make a difference.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: Good balance.  As you probably know drink this slightly chilled so that the nutty complex flavor can be enjoyed.
Pilsner is not my favorite beer.  I found this to be better than Miller but not spectacular
